{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17620563","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17620563"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:44:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:44:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16633"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16633","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16633"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.24,0.14,0.52,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9324"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76517"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9324","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9324"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16633"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62014"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5311"},{"type":"tags","id":"8503"},{"type":"tags","id":"10106"},{"type":"tags","id":"10146"},{"type":"tags","id":"10602"},{"type":"tags","id":"10618"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22097"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22785"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76517","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76517"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EMedroxyprogesterone acetate is a commonly prescribed synthetic progestogen used in various gynaecological conditions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary mechanism of action of medroxyprogesterone acetate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Directly inhibits ovarian steroidogenesis","Maintains the endometrium in the proliferative phase","Stimulates follicle-stimulating hormone release","Binds to progesterone receptors to suppress endometrial proliferation","Increases endometrial prostaglandin synthesis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary mechanism of action of medroxyprogesterone acetate involves \u003Cstrong\u003Ebinding to progesterone receptors to suppress endometrial proliferation\u003C/strong\u003E. This leads to decidualisation and atrophy of the endometrium, making it unsuitable for implantation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirectly inhibits ovarian steroidogenesis\u003C/strong\u003E - Any effect on ovarian function is indirect through suppression of gonadotropins\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaintains the endometrium in the proliferative phase\u003C/strong\u003E - Medroxyprogesterone acetate transitions the endometrium from the proliferative phase to the secretory phase. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStimulates follicle-stimulating hormone release\u003C/strong\u003E - It actually suppresses gonadotropin release through negative feedback\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases endometrial prostaglandin synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E - Medroxyprogesterone typically reduces prostaglandin synthesis in the endometrium\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdditional effects include suppression of gonadotropin secretion through negative feedback at the hypothalamic-pituitary axis, which contributes to its contraceptive efficacy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medroxyprogesterone acetate is a synthetic progestogen that acts primarily by binding to progesterone receptors.","The main therapeutic effects of medroxyprogesterone acetate include endometrial suppression and inhibition of gonadotropin secretion.","Common clinical uses include contraception and management of abnormal uterine bleeding"],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62014"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16633"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62014","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62014"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T16:13:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T16:14:26+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9324"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76517"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"a